OL,6,FThe document did not propose a four-
OL,7,Fday week but committed the party to
OL,8,Fbanning zero-hours contracts,
OL,9,Freplacing them with documents which
OL,10,Freflect the number of hours an
OL,11,Femployee regularly works.
OL,13,FIt also proposed a "genuine living
OL,14,Fwage", and an end to "fire and rehire"
OL,15,Fpractices where workers are laid off
OL,16,Fand then re-employed on new terms.
